### ============================================================
### BFF: Venues — public read API
###
### Read-only, no auth. `q` is a case-insensitive substring
### match on the venue name. Sortable: name, slug, city.
### ============================================================

### List venues (default page 0, size 20, sort name)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues
Accept: application/json

> {%
    client.test("status is 200", function () {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "Expected 200 OK");
    });
    if (response.body.content.length > 0) {
        client.global.set("venue_slug", response.body.content[0].slug);
    }
%}

### List venues — pagination + sort (name desc)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues?page=0&size=5&sort=name,desc
Accept: application/json

### Search venues by name (case-insensitive substring)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues?q=astra
Accept: application/json

### Unknown/malicious sort is ignored (falls back to default order, not a 500)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues?sort=name;DROP TABLE events.venue;--
Accept: application/json

### Get venue by slug (uses the slug captured from the list request above)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues/{{venue_slug}}
Accept: application/json

### Get venue by unknown slug (expect 404)
GET {{bff-host}}/venues/does-not-exist
Accept: application/json
